chatgpt.evidence:
Page 1197, Section VI (Algorithm 1): "Input: φ: RNN to be tested" and algorithm loop showing selection and mutation against that φ ("x' ← m(x)", "if ||orig(x) - x'||2 ≤ r_oracle and φ(x) ≠ φ(x') then Tadv ← Tadv ∪ {x'}");
Page 1197, Section VI-B2b (Targeted Mutation / Fitness): "For the three classes of test conditions (BC, SC, TC) ... we define the following fitness function ... JBC(x) = αmax - Nm(ξs,a_{x,t}) ... JTC(x) = Σ_{j=1}^w dist(Nz(ĥξs_{x,j}), u_j)" (fitness is computed from structural values of the model for input x, i.e., per‑model guidance);
Page 1202, Section VII-F (Comparison with DeepStellar): "We start from 100 seeds drawn from training set and generate 100 000 test cases by DeepStellar and TESTRNN, respectively. The test suites are evaluated for the coverage rate and number of adversarial samples." (generation and evaluation are performed per tool on the same model; no cross‑model reuse of discovered inputs is described);
Page 1201, Section VII-C1 (Detecting adversarial samples): "...we use TC as the termination condition to generate a test suite and calculate the adversarial rate. To achieve the high coverage of test metrics, we use genetic algorithm for test case generation..." (describes adversarial discovery per tested model; no experiment shows applying inputs found on one model to other models).

